<title>USA: Atria Communities completes acquisition.</title>
<headline>Atria Communities completes acquisition.</headline>
<dateline>LOUISVILLE, Ky 1997-04-01</dateline>
<text>
<p>Atria Communities Inc said on Tuesday it had completed its acquisition of American ElderServe Corp.</p>
<p>The value of the deal, as previously announced, was about $30 million including a combination of stock and cash plus debt assumption, the company said.</p>
<p>American ElderServe, a privately-held company based in Atlanta, Ga., operates 12 assisted living communities and has six additional facilities scheduled to open in 1997, Atria said.</p>
